Jeffrey, you have a lot of knowledge--some more accurate then others, but you shouln't mix time frames.  Interest's change. Your posting is an illustration that a little--superficial and disorganized---knowledge is a dangerous thing indeed.<br><br>
&lt;&lt;If the American government cared about freedom and democracy, why don't we have sanctions against Nigeria. &gt;&gt;<br>
Was this the case during the time frame of Viet Nam?  If so, why not answer the question yourself, if not, it's a wrong mix.  Ditto Burma, Indonesia.<br><br>
&lt;&lt;We fought the Persian Gulf War to restore one of the only absolute monarchies on the planet.&gt;&gt;<br>
   We didn't fight the war to restore a monarcy.  We did it so that Iraq wouldn't have a strangle hold on the oil there.<br><br>
&lt;&lt; Turkey has engaged in genocide against Armenians, &gt;&gt;<br>
     That was circa World War 1.  Really now.  A little perspective.  Bending facts to fit an argument is a cheap shot.  We supported Stalin against Hitler--not because we loved Stalin or admired his government, but because we felt that Hitler posed the greatest threat---AT THAT TIME.<br><br>
&lt;&lt; The United States overthrew the first democratically elected leader of Chile.&gt;&gt;<br>
   Not quite true.  I was there.  We were involved and supported the Push, but the military overthru him and the people wanted him out.  I remember a march of women waving dead chickens in the face of soldiers---as their opinion of their courage and manhood.<br><br>
&lt;&lt; The United States trained the death squads of El Salvador which slaughtered whole villages.&gt;&gt;<br>
   Been there seveal times.  Wife from there.  The US DID NOT train Death Squads.  That's pure Left Wing BS.  If we'd wanted to we wouldn't have---why?  It wouldn't have been necessary.  Anyone who thinks the Latins &quot;have to be trained in Death Squads and torture&quot; etc. doesn't have a clue about them, their culture or their history.  <br><br>
 &lt;&lt;Since when has the American government ever cared remotely about democracy or freedom anywhere in the world? &gt;&gt;<br>
No country has been more willing to put-up and fight to defend and/or help poor nations then has the US---not for profit, and not for praise, but because we could and were willing to do so.  Have you forgoten, Spanish-American War, WW1, WW2, Korea, Panama, Grenada, Guatamala, Haiti, Somolia, and now Bosnia???  If the US did it for profit, where's the profet from our helping and restoring these countrues to include Germany and Japan.<br><br>
&lt;&lt;The Vietnam War had absolutely nothing to do with democracy or freedom.&gt;&gt;<br>
 That's your opinion and you are welcomed to it.  Wrong as it is.<br><br>
&lt;&lt;We slaughtered two million Vietnamese. &gt;&gt;<br>
    Really--says who?   Get your facts straight and don't forget the 1.5 million murdered Cambodians---because we WEREN'T  there.  <br>
